{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"00d38ff4-7cdf-4074-be1d-062fb846f8c9","content":"The tutorial is **partially outdated** — it likely targets Xamarin.Forms, not .NET MAUI.\n\n**1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ **Correct for .NET MAUI / .NET 10.**\n\nYou need the iOS platform-specific namespace:\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\nThis adds padding so content avoids the notch/home indicator.\n\n**2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid** — ❌ **Does not exist in .NET MAUI.**\n\nThis was a Xamarin.Forms property. In .NET MAUI, if you want a background image to extend behind the safe area while keeping other content safe, the typical pattern is:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"...\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Background fills entire screen -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n        <!-- Content respects safe area via manual padding -->\n        <StackLayout Padding=\"20,50,20,20\">\n            <!-- your content -->\n        </StackLayout>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nSet `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` (or omit it — false is the default), then manually pad your foreground content to avoid the notch area.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"783c135c-562e-4fca-bb98-6a14a148ff0c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory seems to be empty or the view didn't return anything useful. Let me answer from my knowledge about .NET MAUI safe area handling.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the correct approach for handling safe areas on iOS has evolved:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is the **correct** platform-specific attached property for .NET MAUI. You need the iOS namespace: `xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"`. This tells the page to respect safe area insets (avoiding the notch, home indicator, etc.).\n\n\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` doesn't exist in .NET MAUI—that was a Xamarin.Forms property. For ignoring safe areas on specific elements, you'd need to handle it differently depending on whether you're working at the page level with `UseSafeArea` or managing layout padding manually. So the key distinction is that `IgnoreSafeArea` was a Xamarin.Forms property that doesn't exist in .NET MAUI—only `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` is valid. To extend a background image behind the safe area in MAUI, I'd need to disable `UseSafeArea` on the page and then manually manage padding for the content that should respect the safe area, using something like an AbsoluteLayout or Grid where the background fills the entire space.","outputTokens":1070,"requestId":"4836:1B2DC6:A1C5E2:BD9E31:69F3FE14"},"id":"95dbe2b1-4dc6-4d7c-a380-389d06626b2a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:13:12.624Z","parentId":"d25eaa7d-5d2e-4b9c-846a-17fa98cc59a4"}
